</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">To prevent service calls and replacement of the runner block it is essential that the lubricators are replaced on time. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Replacement of the lubricators will preferably be done by the customer when indicated on the operator panel. If a customer is not capable to replace the lubricators the technician can perform this task during a regular service visit. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">To create a uniform print in the carriage direction the velocity of the carriage needs to be uniform. This way the droplets will arrive next to each other on the media. In case of the velocity of the carriage is not stable, it’s possible the droplets will end on top of each other or too far apart. This will lead to lighter/darker areas in the carriage direction depending on the position of the droplets. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The stability of the velocity of the carriage is controlled by the ruler and the ruler encoder. However, in the case of Carriage vibrations, the velocity shows small fluctuations which will result in undefined local distortions in the print. In most cases, carriage vibrations are caused by bad lubrication of the guidance. This will result in local friction that can reduce the speed of the carriage locally. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In the C1630 and onwards there are SDS-tests 4-6-028 and 4-6-035 to determine the component which is responsible for this pattern. This test is however not finished yet and still under investigation by R&amp;D. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-E296D1A5-6E40-45FA-8995-87FBE4000791.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
